{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851763973,"sessionID":"ses_286fd8827ffeNZ24Cl7YElY69e","part":{"id":"prt_d790378dc001wK25Oe0qie3830","messageID":"msg_d790366a8001N7pjiExME3G1yF","sessionID":"ses_286fd8827ffeNZ24Cl7YElY69e","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c834dba2985243758cdc969d32923040","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/router`\n4: Language: Go\n5: Size: M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Router session management subsystem, providing session lifecycle management, sandbox routing, reverse proxy, JWT authentication, unified error handling, and middleware support for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocation requests.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: SessionManager Interface\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** the Router needs to manage sessions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter  \n20: **WHEN** handling session-based routing requests  \n21: **THEN** SessionManager interface shall be properly defined with GetSandboxBySession method\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: SessionManager interface definition\n27: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n28: WHEN reading the SessionManager interface\n29: THEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n30: \n31: // Scenario 2: SessionManager implementation\n32: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n33: WHEN reading the sessionManager struct\n34: THEN it SHALL contain fields: storeClient Store, workloadMgrAddr string, httpClient *http.Client\n35: \n36: // Scenario 3: NewSessionManager constructor\n37: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n38: WHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient Store)\n39: THEN it SHALL read WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL from environment variable\n40: AND it SHALL return error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL is not set\n41: AND it SHALL configure HTTP client with 2 minute timeout and HTTP2 transport\n42: \n43: // Scenario 4: NewSessionManager environment requirement\n44: GIVEN WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable not set\n45: WHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient)\n46: THEN it SHALL return error with message \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is required\"\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### REQ-002: GetSandboxBySession Method\n52: \n53: **GIVEN** a session needs to be looked up or created  \n54: **WHEN** invoking GetSandboxBySession  \n55: **THEN** the method shall return existing sandbox or create a new one\n56: \n57: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // Scenario 1: Existing session lookup\n61: GIVEN a sessionManager with Store containing session \"existing-session\"\n62: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"existing-session\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n63: THEN it SHALL call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"existing-session\")\n64: AND it SHALL return the existing SandboxInfo\n65: \n66: // Scenario 2: Empty sessionID creates new sandbox\n67: GIVEN a sessionManager with empty sessionID parameter\n68: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"default\", \"test-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n69: THEN it SHALL call createSandbox to create new sandbox\n70: AND it SHALL NOT call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID\n71: \n72: // Scenario 3: Session not found error\n73: GIVEN a sessionManager with Store returning error for session \"nonexistent\"\n74: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"nonexistent\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n75: THEN it SHALL return SessionNotFoundError with SessionID field set\n76: \n77: // Scenario 4: Namespace and name passed to createSandbox\n78: GIVEN a sessionManager creating new sandbox\n79: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"my-namespace\", \"my-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n80: THEN createSandbox SHALL receive namespace=\"my-namespace\", name=\"my-runtime\", kind=\"AgentRuntime\"\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ### REQ-003: CreateSandbox Method\n86: \n87: **GIVEN** a new sandbox needs to be created via WorkloadManager  \n88: **WHEN** calling createSandbox  \n89: **THEN** it shall send HTTP POST request to WorkloadManager and store the result\n90: \n91: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n92: \n93: ```go\n94: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime endpoint selection\n95: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"AgentRuntime\"\n96: WHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\n97: THEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/agent-runtime\"\n98: \n99: // Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter endpoint selection\n100: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"CodeInterpreter\"\n101: WHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\n102: THEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/code-interpreter\"\n103: \n104: // Scenario 3: Unsupported kind error\n105: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"UnsupportedKind\"\n106: WHEN executing the method\n107: THEN it SHALL return error \"unsupported kind: UnsupportedKind\"\n108: \n109: // Scenario 4: Request body marshaling\n110: GIVEN createSandbox called\n111: WHEN building the HTTP request body\n112: THEN body SHALL be JSON marshaled CreateSandboxRequest{Kind, Name, Namespace}\n113: \n114: // Scenario 5: Request validation\n115: GIVEN CreateSandboxRequest with invalid parameters\n116: WHEN calling Validate()\n117: THEN it SHALL return error if Kind is not AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n118: AND it SHALL return error if Namespace is empty\n119: AND it SHALL return error if Name is empty\n120: \n121: // Scenario 6: WorkloadManager HTTP error\n122: GIVEN WorkloadManager returning HTTP 500\n123: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n124: THEN it SHALL return WorkloadManagerError with StatusCode 500\n125: \n126: // Scenario 7: Empty sessionId in response\n127: GIVEN WorkloadManager returning response with empty sessionId\n128: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n129: THEN it SHALL return error \"empty sessionId in response\"\n130: \n131: // Scenario 8: Sandbox stored in Store\n132: GIVEN successful WorkloadManager response\n133: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n134: THEN it SHALL call storeClient.StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n135: AND sandbox SHALL have Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-004: Store Interface\n141: \n142: **GIVEN** the Router needs to persist and retrieve session data  \n143: **WHEN** managing session storage  \n144: **THEN** Store interface shall be properly defined\n145: \n146: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n147: \n148: ```go\n149: // Scenario 1: Store interface definition\n150: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n151: WHEN reading the Store interface\n152: THEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n153: AND it SHALL define StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n154: AND it SHALL define UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n155: \n156: // Scenario 2: Store used by SessionManager\n157: GIVEN sessionManager struct\n158: WHEN reading the implementation\n159: THEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n160: \n161: // Scenario 3: Store used by Server\n162: GIVEN Server struct\n163: WHEN reading the implementation\n164: THEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### REQ-005: Service Account Token\n170: \n171: **GIVEN** Router needs to authenticate with WorkloadManager  \n172: **WHEN** sending requests to WorkloadManager  \n173: **THEN** it shall use Kubernetes service account token\n174: \n175: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n176: \n177: ```go\n178: // Scenario 1: readServiceAccountToken function\n179: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n180: WHEN reading readServiceAccountToken function\n181: THEN it SHALL read from \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n182: AND it SHALL return trimmed token string\n183: \n184: // Scenario 2: Token added to request header\n185: GIVEN createSandbox with valid service account token\n186: WHEN building HTTP request\n187: THEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + saToken\n188: \n189: // Scenario 3: Token read error handled gracefully\n190: GIVEN service account token file not existing\n191: WHEN readServiceAccountToken returns error\n192: THEN request SHALL proceed without Authorization header\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### REQ-006: Router Server Configuration\n198: \n199: **GIVEN** Router needs configurable HTTP server  \n200: **WHEN** setting up the server  \n201: **THEN** Config struct shall support all necessary options\n202: \n203: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n204: \n205: ```go\n206: // Scenario 1: Config struct definition\n207: GIVEN pkg/router/config.go\n208: WHEN reading the Config struct\n209: THEN it SHALL contain fields: Port string, EnableTLS bool, TLSCert string, TLSKey string, MaxConcurrentRequests int, Debug bool\n210: \n211: // Scenario 2: DefaultConfig function\n212: GIVEN pkg/router/config.go\n213: WHEN calling DefaultConfig()\n214: THEN it SHALL return Config with Port \":8080\", EnableTLS false, MaxConcurrentRequests 1000, Debug false\n215: \n216: // Scenario 3: Server constructor with nil config\n217: GIVEN NewServer called with nil config\n218: WHEN constructing Server\n219: THEN DefaultConfig SHALL be used\n220: \n221: // Scenario 4: MaxConcurrentRequests default\n222: GIVEN Config with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n223: WHEN constructing Server\n224: THEN MaxConcurrentRequests SHALL be set to 1000\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### REQ-007: Router Server Structure\n230: \n231: **GIVEN** Router needs HTTP server with Gin framework  \n232: **WHEN** constructing the Server  \n233: **THEN** Server struct shall contain all necessary components\n234: \n235: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // Scenario 1: Server struct definition\n239: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n240: WHEN reading the Server struct\n241: THEN it SHALL contain fields: config *Config, engine *gin.Engine, httpServer *http.Server, sessionManager SessionManager, storeClient Store, httpTransport *http.Transport, jwtManager *JWTManager, logger Logger\n242: \n243: // Scenario 2: Server constructor\n244: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n245: WHEN calling NewServer(config, sessionManager, storeClient, jwtManager, logger)\n246: THEN it SHALL return *Server with all fields initialized\n247: AND gin.Engine SHALL be created with gin.New()\n248: AND http.Server SHALL have ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n249: \n250: // Scenario 3: Gin mode configuration\n251: GIVEN Config with Debug false\n252: WHEN constructing Server\n253: THEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.ReleaseMode\n254: \n255: // Scenario 4: Gin mode with Debug true\n256: GIVEN Config with Debug true\n257: WHEN constructing Server\n258: THEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.DebugMode\n259: \n260: // Scenario 5: registerRoutes called\n261: GIVEN NewServer constructing Server\n262: WHEN initialization completes\n263: THEN registerRoutes SHALL be called\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ### REQ-008: Router Route Registration\n269: \n270: **GIVEN** Router needs RESTful API endpoints  \n271: **WHEN** registering routes  \n272: **THEN** all endpoints shall be properly registered with middleware\n273: \n274: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: // Scenario 1: Health endpoints registered\n278: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n279: WHEN reading route registration\n280: THEN /health/live endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\n281: AND /health/ready endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\n282: \n283: // Scenario 2: AgentRuntime invocation endpoints\n284: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n285: WHEN reading route registration\n286: THEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n287: \n288: // Scenario 3: CodeInterpreter invocation endpoints\n289: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n290: WHEN reading route registration\n291: THEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n292: \n293: // Scenario 4: Middleware applied to v1 group\n294: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n295: WHEN reading v1 route group\n296: THEN concurrencyLimitMiddleware SHALL be applied\n297: AND loggingMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\n298: AND recoveryMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\n299: ```\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ### REQ-009: Health Endpoints\n304: \n305: **GIVEN** Kubernetes needs liveness and readiness probes  \n306: **WHEN** implementing health endpoints  \n307: **THEN** proper health responses shall be returned\n308: \n309: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // Scenario 1: handleHealthLive endpoint\n313: GIVEN GET request to /health/live\n314: WHEN handler executes\n315: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n316: \n317: // Scenario 2: handleHealthReady with SessionManager\n318: GIVEN GET request to /health/ready with valid SessionManager\n319: WHEN handler executes\n320: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n321: \n322: // Scenario 3: handleHealthReady without SessionManager\n323: GIVEN GET request to /health/ready with nil SessionManager\n324: WHEN handler executes\n325: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with JSON {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### REQ-010: Invoke Handler\n331: \n332: **GIVEN** invocation requests need to be routed to sandbox  \n333: **WHEN** handling AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter invocation  \n334: **THEN** request shall be proxied to the correct sandbox endpoint\n335: \n336: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: // Scenario 1: handleAgentInvoke delegates to handleInvoke\n340: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n341: WHEN reading handleAgentInvoke method\n342: THEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n343: \n344: // Scenario 2: handleCodeInterpreterInvoke delegates\n345: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n346: WHEN reading handleCodeInterpreterInvoke method\n347: THEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.CodeInterpreterKind)\n348: \n349: // Scenario 3: SessionID from header\n350: GIVEN invocation request\n351: WHEN handleInvoke reads sessionID\n352: THEN it SHALL read from \"x-agentcube-session-id\" header\n353: \n354: // Scenario 4: Parameters extracted from URL\n355: GIVEN invocation request to /v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-runtime/invocations/api/test\n356: WHEN handleInvoke processes request\n357: THEN namespace SHALL be \"default\"\n358: AND name SHALL be \"my-runtime\"\n359: AND invocationPath SHALL be \"/api/test\"\n360: \n361: // Scenario 5: GetSandboxBySession called\n362: GIVEN handleInvoke with valid parameters\n363: WHEN processing request\n364: THEN sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession SHALL be called with ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind\n365: \n366: // Scenario 6: No entry point error\n367: GIVEN sandbox with empty EntryPoints\n368: WHEN handleInvoke processes request\n369: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 404 with JSON {\"error\": \"no entry point configured\", \"code\": \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"}\n370: \n371: // Scenario 7: UpdateSessionLastActivity before proxy\n372: GIVEN successful sandbox lookup\n373: WHEN before proxying request\n374: THEN storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity SHALL be called with current time\n375: \n376: // Scenario 8: Entry point selection\n377: GIVEN sandbox with multiple entry points\n378: WHEN selecting entry point\n379: THEN selectEntryPoint SHALL be called with entryPoints and invocationPath\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ### REQ-011: Entry Point Selection\n385: \n386: **GIVEN** sandbox has multiple entry points  \n387: **WHEN** routing request to entry point  \n388: **THEN** correct entry point shall be selected based on path prefix\n389: \n390: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n391: \n392: ```go\n393: // Scenario 1: selectEntryPoint matching path\n394: GIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/api/v1/resource\"\n395: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n396: THEN it SHALL return entry point with Path \"/api\"\n397: \n398: // Scenario 2: selectEntryPoint no matching path returns first\n399: GIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/other/path\"\n400: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n401: THEN it SHALL return first entry point as default\n402: \n403: // Scenario 3: selectEntryPoint empty entry points\n404: GIVEN empty entry points slice\n405: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n406: THEN it SHALL return nil\n407: \n408: // Scenario 4: buildTargetURL with protocol\n409: GIVEN entry point with Protocol \"http\" and Endpoint \"localhost:8080\"\n410: WHEN calling buildTargetURL\n411: THEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:8080\"\n412: \n413: // Scenario 5: buildTargetURL with endpoint containing protocol\n414: GIVEN entry point with empty Protocol and Endpoint \"http://localhost:9000\"\n415: WHEN calling buildTargetURL\n416: THEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:9000\"\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ### REQ-012: Reverse Proxy\n422: \n423: **GIVEN** requests need to be proxied to sandbox  \n424: **WHEN** implementing reverse proxy  \n425: **THEN** proper headers and response handling shall be implemented\n426: \n427: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n428: \n429: ```go\n430: // Scenario 1: ReverseProxyWrapper struct\n431: GIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go\n432: WHEN reading ReverseProxyWrapper struct\n433: THEN it SHALL contain director, modifyResponse, errorHandler function fields\n434: \n435: // Scenario 2: Director sets target URL\n436: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\n437: WHEN modifying request\n438: THEN req.URL.Scheme SHALL be set to target.Scheme\n439: AND req.URL.Host SHALL be set to target.Host\n440: AND req.URL.Path SHALL be set correctly\n441: \n442: // Scenario 3: Director sets forwarded headers\n443: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\n444: WHEN modifying request\n445: THEN X-Forwarded-Host header SHALL be set\n446: AND X-Forwarded-Proto header SHALL be set\n447: AND X-Forwarded-For header SHALL be set\n448: \n449: // Scenario 4: Director sets JWT Authorization\n450: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper with non-empty jwt parameter\n451: WHEN modifying request\n452: THEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + jwt\n453: \n454: // Scenario 5: ModifyResponse sets session header\n455: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper ModifyResponse function\n456: WHEN modifying response\n457: THEN x-agentcube-session-id header SHALL be set\n458: \n459: // Scenario 6: ErrorHandler connection refused\n460: GIVEN error message containing \"connection refused\"\n461: WHEN ErrorHandler handles error\n462: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 502 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}\n463: \n464: // Scenario 7: ErrorHandler timeout\n465: GIVEN error message containing \"timeout\"\n466: WHEN ErrorHandler handles error\n467: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 504 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}\n468: ```\n469: \n470: ---\n471: \n472: ### REQ-013: JWT Manager\n473: \n474: **GIVEN** Router needs JWT token generation for sandbox authentication  \n475: **WHEN** implementing JWT management  \n476: **THEN** JWTManager shall generate RS256 signed tokens\n477: \n478: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n479: \n480: ```go\n481: // Scenario 1: JWTManager struct\n482: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n483: WHEN reading JWTManager struct\n484: THEN it SHALL contain privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey and publicKey *rsa.PublicKey fields\n485: \n486: // Scenario 2: NewJWTManager constructor\n487: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n488: WHEN calling NewJWTManager()\n489: THEN it SHALL generate RSA key with size 2048\n490: AND it SHALL return *JWTManager with keys initialized\n491: \n492: // Scenario 3: GenerateToken method\n493: GIVEN JWTManager instance\n494: WHEN calling GenerateToken(claims)\n495: THEN token SHALL use jwt.SigningMethodRS256\n496: AND token SHALL contain exp claim with 5 minute expiration\n497: AND token SHALL contain iat claim with current time\n498: AND token SHALL contain iss claim \"agentcube-router\"\n499: AND custom claims SHALL be added to token\n500: \n501: // Scenario 4: JWTSigningError on failure\n502: GIVEN JWTManager signing failure\n503: WHEN GenerateToken returns error\n504: THEN it SHALL return JWTSigningError wrapping the underlying error\n505: \n506: // Scenario 5: RSA constants\n507: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n508: WHEN reading constants\n509: THEN rsaKeySize SHALL be 2048\n510: AND jwtExpiration SHALL be 5 minutes\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ### REQ-014: Identity Namespace\n516: \n517: **GIVEN** Router needs configurable namespace  \n518: **WHEN** setting identity namespace  \n519: **THEN** it shall read from environment variable\n520: \n521: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n522: \n523: ```go\n524: // Scenario 1: IdentityNamespace default\n525: GIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable not set\n526: WHEN init() function executes\n527: THEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"default\"\n528: \n529: // Scenario 2: IdentityNamespace from environment\n530: GIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable set to \"my-namespace\"\n531: WHEN init() function executes\n532: THEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"my-namespace\"\n533: \n534: // Scenario 3: IdentitySecretName constant\n535: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n536: WHEN reading constants\n537: THEN IdentitySecretName SHALL be \"picod-router-identity\"\n538: \n539: // Scenario 4: Key data key constants\n540: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n541: WHEN reading constants\n542: THEN PrivateKeyDataKey SHALL be \"private.pem\"\n543: AND PublicKeyDataKey SHALL be \"public.pem\"\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### REQ-015: Custom Error Types\n549: \n550: **GIVEN** Router needs unified error handling  \n551: **WHEN** defining error types  \n552: **THEN** all errors shall implement APIStatus interface\n553: \n554: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n555: \n556: ```go\n557: // Scenario 1: APIStatus interface\n558: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n559: WHEN reading APIStatus interface\n560: THEN it SHALL define Status() int\n561: AND it SHALL define Code() string\n562: AND it SHALL define Message() string\n563: \n564: // Scenario 2: SessionNotFoundError\n565: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n566: WHEN reading SessionNotFoundError struct\n567: THEN it SHALL contain SessionID string field\n568: AND Status() SHALL return 404\n569: AND Code() SHALL return \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n570: AND Message() SHALL return \"session not found\"\n571: \n572: // Scenario 3: SandboxUnreachableError\n573: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n574: WHEN reading SandboxUnreachableError struct\n575: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n576: AND Status() SHALL return 502\n577: AND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE\"\n578: \n579: // Scenario 4: SandboxTimeoutError\n580: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n581: WHEN reading SandboxTimeoutError struct\n582: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n583: AND Status() SHALL return 504\n584: AND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_TIMEOUT\"\n585: \n586: // Scenario 5: JWTSigningError\n587: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n588: WHEN reading JWTSigningError struct\n589: THEN it SHALL contain Err error field\n590: AND Status() SHALL return 500\n591: AND Code() SHALL return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n592: \n593: // Scenario 6: ServerOverloadedError\n594: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n595: WHEN reading ServerOverloadedError struct\n596: THEN Status() SHALL return 429\n597: AND Code() SHALL return \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n598: \n599: // Scenario 7: NoEntryPointError\n600: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n601: WHEN reading NoEntryPointError struct\n602: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n603: AND Status() SHALL return 404\n604: AND Code() SHALL return \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"\n605: \n606: // Scenario 8: WorkloadManagerError\n607: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n608: WHEN reading WorkloadManagerError struct\n609: THEN it SHALL contain StatusCode int and Msg string fields\n610: AND Code() SHALL return \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR\"\n611: ```\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: ### REQ-016: Concurrency Limit Middleware\n616: \n617: **GIVEN** Router needs to limit concurrent requests  \n618: **WHEN** implementing concurrency middleware  \n619: **THEN** requests exceeding limit shall receive 429 response\n620: \n621: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n622: \n623: ```go\n624: // Scenario 1: concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\n625: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n626: WHEN reading concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\n627: THEN it SHALL use semaphore channel for concurrency control\n628: \n629: // Scenario 2: Request allowed within limit\n630: GIVEN concurrency limit of 1000\n631: WHEN request arrives within limit\n632: THEN request SHALL proceed via c.Next()\n633: \n634: // Scenario 3: Request rejected over limit\n635: GIVEN concurrency limit exceeded\n636: WHEN request arrives\n637: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 429\n638: AND JSON body SHALL contain {\"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}\n639: AND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n640: \n641: // Scenario 4: Default limit when config invalid\n642: GIVEN maxConcurrent <= 0\n643: WHEN middleware initialized\n644: THEN limit SHALL be set to 1000\n645: ```\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ### REQ-017: Logging Middleware\n650: \n651: **GIVEN** requests need structured logging  \n652: **WHEN** implementing logging middleware  \n653: **THEN** request details shall be logged\n654: \n655: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n656: \n657: ```go\n658: // Scenario 1: loggingMiddleware function\n659: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n660: WHEN reading loggingMiddleware function\n661: THEN it SHALL capture request start time\n662: AND it SHALL call c.Next() and then log\n663: \n664: // Scenario 2: Log fields captured\n665: GIVEN loggingMiddleware processing request\n666: WHEN request completes\n667: THEN logger.Info SHALL be called\n668: AND log SHALL contain method, path, status, duration fields\n669: \n670: // Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\n671: GIVEN loggingMiddleware with nil logger\n672: WHEN request completes\n673: THEN no logging SHALL occur\n674: ```\n675: \n676: ---\n677: \n678: ### REQ-018: Recovery Middleware\n679: \n680: **GIVEN** panics in handlers need recovery  \n681: **WHEN** implementing recovery middleware  \n682: **THEN** panics shall be caught and 500 response returned\n683: \n684: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n685: \n686: ```go\n687: // Scenario 1: recoveryMiddleware function\n688: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n689: WHEN reading recoveryMiddleware function\n690: THEN it SHALL use defer with recover()\n691: \n692: // Scenario 2: Panic recovered\n693: GIVEN handler panics\n694: WHEN recoveryMiddleware catches panic\n695: THEN logger.Error SHALL be called with error, path, method fields\n696: AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with JSON {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\n697: AND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n698: \n699: // Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\n700: GIVEN recoveryMiddleware with nil logger\n701: WHEN panic occurs\n702: THEN no logging SHALL occur\n703: AND HTTP 500 response SHALL still be returned\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ---\n707: \n708: ### REQ-019: Server Lifecycle\n709: \n710: **GIVEN** Server needs graceful startup and shutdown  \n711: **WHEN** managing server lifecycle  \n712: **THEN** Start and Stop methods shall be properly implemented\n713: \n714: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n715: \n716: ```go\n717: // Scenario 1: Start method without TLS\n718: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS false\n719: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n720: THEN httpServer.ListenAndServe SHALL be called\n721: AND waitForShutdown SHALL be started in goroutine\n722: \n723: // Scenario 2: Start method with TLS\n724: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS true and valid TLSCert/TLSKey\n725: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n726: THEN httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS SHALL be called\n727: \n728: // Scenario 3: TLS config validation\n729: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS true but missing TLSCert or TLSKey\n730: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n731: THEN it SHALL return error \"TLS cert and key are required when EnableTLS is true\"\n732: \n733: // Scenario 4: waitForShutdown behavior\n734: GIVEN Server.Start called\n735: WHEN ctx.Done() channel closes\n736: THEN shutdownCtx SHALL be created with 10 second timeout\n737: AND httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called\n738: \n739: // Scenario 5: Stop method\n740: GIVEN running Server\n741: WHEN calling Stop()\n742: THEN httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called with 10 second timeout context\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ---\n746: \n747: ### REQ-020: Logger Interface\n748: \n749: **GIVEN** Router needs structured logging  \n750: **WHEN** defining logger abstraction  \n751: **THEN** Logger interface shall support Info, Error, Warning methods\n752: \n753: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n754: \n755: ```go\n756: // Scenario 1: Logger interface definition\n757: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n758: WHEN reading Logger interface\n759: THEN it SHALL define Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n760: AND it SHALL define Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n761: AND it SHALL define Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n762: \n763: // Scenario 2: Logger used in Server\n764: GIVEN Server struct\n765: WHEN reading the implementation\n766: THEN logger field SHALL be of type Logger\n767: \n768: // Scenario 3: Logger used in middleware\n769: GIVEN loggingMiddleware and recoveryMiddleware\n770: WHEN logging events\n771: THEN Logger interface methods SHALL be used\n772: ```\n773: \n774: ---\n775: \n776: ### REQ-021: Error Handling in Server\n777: \n778: **GIVEN** Server needs unified error responses  \n779: **WHEN** handling errors in handlers  \n780: **THEN** handleGetSandboxError shall map errors to correct HTTP codes\n781: \n782: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n783: \n784: ```go\n785: // Scenario 1: Kubernetes NotFound error\n786: GIVEN apierrors.IsNotFound(err) true\n787: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n788: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 404\n789: \n790: // Scenario 2: APIStatus error\n791: GIVEN error implementing apierrors.APIStatus\n792: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n793: THEN HTTP status code SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\n794: AND message SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\n795: AND HTTP 500 message SHALL be \"internal server error\"\n796: \n797: // Scenario 3: Router APIStatus error\n798: GIVEN error implementing router.APIStatus\n799: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n800: THEN response SHALL use routerErr.Status() for HTTP code\n801: AND JSON SHALL contain error, code fields\n802: \n803: // Scenario 4: Unknown error\n804: GIVEN error not implementing APIStatus\n805: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n806: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 500 with {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\n807: ```\n808: \n809: ---\n810: \n811: ### REQ-022: Unit Tests\n812: \n813: **GIVEN** implementation needs test coverage  \n814: **WHEN** verifying functionality  \n815: **THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n816: \n817: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n818: \n819: ```go\n820: // Scenario 1: session_manager tests\n821: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager_test.go\n822: WHEN running tests\n823: THEN NewSessionManager tests SHALL verify WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL requirement\n824: AND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify existing session lookup\n825: AND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify session creation\n826: AND createSandbox tests SHALL verify endpoint selection\n827: AND tests SHALL verify error handling\n828: \n829: // Scenario 2: server tests\n830: GIVEN pkg/router/server_test.go\n831: WHEN running tests\n832: THEN NewServer tests SHALL verify constructor with various configs\n833: AND health endpoint tests SHALL verify /health/live and /health/ready\n834: AND route registration tests SHALL verify all routes present\n835: AND lifecycle tests SHALL verify Start/Stop/GracefulShutdown\n836: AND TLS tests SHALL verify TLS requirement validation\n837: \n838: // Scenario 3: errors tests\n839: GIVEN pkg/router/errors_test.go\n840: WHEN running tests\n841: THEN all error types SHALL have tests verifying Error(), Status(), Code(), Message()\n842: AND APIStatus interface compliance SHALL be tested\n843: \n844: // Scenario 4: reverse_proxy tests\n845: GIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go\n846: WHEN running tests\n847: THEN selectEntryPoint tests SHALL verify path matching\n848: AND buildTargetURL tests SHALL verify URL construction\n849: \n850: // Scenario 5: middleware tests\n851: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware_test.go\n852: WHEN running tests\n853: THEN concurrencyLimit tests SHALL verify limit enforcement\n854: AND logging tests SHALL verify log output\n855: AND recovery tests SHALL verify panic handling\n856: \n857: // Scenario 6: jwt tests\n858: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt_test.go\n859: WHEN running tests\n860: THEN NewJWTManager tests SHALL verify key generation\n861: AND GenerateToken tests SHALL verify token creation and claims\n862: \n863: // Scenario 7: config tests\n864: GIVEN pkg/router/config_test.go\n865: WHEN running tests\n866: THEN DefaultConfig tests SHALL verify default values\n867: ```\n868: \n869: ---\n870: \n871: ### REQ-023: Code Quality\n872: \n873: **GIVEN** code needs to meet quality standards  \n874: **WHEN** running linting and validation  \n875: **THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n876: \n877: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n878: \n879: ```go\n880: // Scenario 1: go vet passes\n881: GIVEN pkg/router/\n882: WHEN running go vet ./pkg/router/...\n883: THEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n884: \n885: // Scenario 2: Build succeeds\n886: GIVEN pkg/router/\n887: WHEN running go build ./pkg/router/...\n888: THEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n889: \n890: // Scenario 3: Test coverage threshold\n891: GIVEN pkg/router/\n892: WHEN running go test -cover ./pkg/router/...\n893: THEN coverage SHALL be greater than 80%\n894: \n895: // Scenario 4: All tests pass\n896: GIVEN pkg/router/\n897: WHEN running go test ./pkg/router/...\n898: THEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n899: ```\n900: \n901: ---\n902: \n903: ### REQ-024: Package Documentation\n904: \n905: **GIVEN** package needs documentation  \n906: **WHEN** organizing package structure  \n907: **THEN** proper documentation shall be present\n908: \n909: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n910: \n911: ```go\n912: // Scenario 1: doc.go file exists\n913: GIVEN pkg/router/\n914: WHEN listing files\n915: THEN doc.go SHALL exist\n916: \n917: // Scenario 2: Interfaces documented\n918: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n919: WHEN reading the file\n920: THEN Store, Logger, SessionManager, JWTManagerInterface, APIStatus interfaces SHALL be defined\n921: ```\n922: \n923: ---\n924: \n925: ### REQ-025: SandboxInfo Types\n926: \n927: **GIVEN** Router uses sandbox info types  \n928: **WHEN** working with sandbox data  \n929: **THEN** types shall support all necessary fields\n930: \n931: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n932: \n933: ```go\n934: // Scenario 1: SandboxInfo struct\n935: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n936: WHEN reading SandboxInfo struct\n937: THEN it SHALL contain Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\n938: AND all fields SHALL have JSON tags\n939: \n940: // Scenario 2: SandboxEntryPoint struct\n941: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n942: WHEN reading SandboxEntryPoint struct\n943: THEN it SHALL contain Path, Protocol, Endpoint fields with JSON tags\n944: \n945: // Scenario 3: CreateSandboxRequest struct\n946: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n947: WHEN reading CreateSandboxRequest struct\n948: THEN it SHALL contain Kind, Name, Namespace fields with JSON tags\n949: AND Validate method SHALL validate all fields\n950: \n951: // Scenario 4: CreateSandboxResponse struct\n952: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n953: WHEN reading CreateSandboxResponse struct\n954: THEN it SHALL contain SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints fields with JSON tags\n955: \n956: // Scenario 5: Kind constants\n957: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n958: WHEN reading constants\n959: THEN AgentRuntimeKind SHALL be \"AgentRuntime\"\n960: AND CodeInterpreterKind SHALL be \"CodeInterpreter\"\n961: AND SandboxKind SHALL be \"Sandbox\"\n962: AND SandboxClaimKind SHALL be \"SandboxClaim\"\n963: ```\n964: \n965: ---\n966: \n967: ## Implementation Files\n968: \n969: | File | Purpose |\n970: |------|---------|\n971: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager implementation with GetSandboxBySession and createSandbox |\n972: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTPServer implementation with Gin framework, routes, and lifecycle |\n973: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | ReverseProxyWrapper, selectEntryPoint, buildTargetURL |\n974: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | concurrencyLimitMiddleware, loggingMiddleware, recoveryMiddleware |\n975: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation and token signing |\n976: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Custom error types implementing APIStatus interface |\n977: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct and DefaultConfig function |\n978: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Interface definitions: Store, Logger, SessionManager, APIStatus |\n979: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n980: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n981: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy and entry point tests |\n982: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n983: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT manager unit tests |\n984: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n985: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n986: | `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | SandboxInfo, SandboxEntryPoint, request/response types |\n987: \n988: ---\n989: \n990: ## Dependencies\n991: \n992: | Package | Purpose |\n993: |---------|---------|\n994: | `net/http` | HTTP server and client |\n995: | `context` | Request context for cancellation |\n996: | `time` | Time handling for sessions and timeouts |\n997: | `encoding/json` | JSON marshaling for requests/responses |\n998: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP router framework |\n999: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT token generation |\n1000: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport support |\n1001: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Kubernetes error types |\n1002: \n1003: ---\n1004: \n1005: ## API Endpoints\n1006: \n1007: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n1008: |----------|--------|---------|\n1009: | `/health/live` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe |\n1010: | `/health/ready` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe |\n1011: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | AgentRuntime invocation proxy |\n1012: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | CodeInterpreter invocation proxy |\n1013: \n1014: ---\n1015: \n1016: ## Error Codes\n1017: \n1018: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n1019: |------|-------------|-------------|\n1020: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session ID not found in store |\n1021: | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | No entry point configured for sandbox |\n1022: | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Sandbox endpoint connection refused |\n1023: | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Sandbox endpoint timeout |\n1024: | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT token signing failure |\n1025: | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrent request limit exceeded |\n1026: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR` | varies | Error from WorkloadManager |\n1027: \n1028: ---\n1029: \n1030: ## Validation Checklist\n1031: \n1032: - [ ] SessionManager correctly creates and retrieves sessions\n1033: - [ ] GetSandboxBySession handles existing sessions and creates new ones\n1034: - [ ] createSandbox sends correct requests to WorkloadManager\n1035: - [ ] Store interface supports session persistence\n1036: - [ ] Service account token correctly added to requests\n1037: - [ ] Server properly configured with Gin framework\n1038: - [ ] All routes registered with correct middleware\n1039: - [ ] Health endpoints respond correctly\n1040: - [ ] Invoke handlers route requests to sandbox entry points\n1041: - [ ] Entry point selection works correctly\n1042: - [ ] Reverse proxy sets proper headers\n1043: - [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens\n1044: - [ ] All error types implement APIStatus interface\n1045: - [ ] Middleware enforces concurrency limit\n1046: - [ ] Logging middleware captures request details\n1047: - [ ] Recovery middleware handles panics\n1048: - [ ] Server lifecycle supports graceful shutdown\n1049: - [ ] Logger interface supports structured logging\n1050: - [ ] Error handling maps to correct HTTP codes\n1051: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n1052: - [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n1053: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n1054: - [ ] All tests pass without failures\n\n(End of file - total 1054 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\nModule: `pkg/router`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Router session management subsystem, providing session lifecycle management, sandbox routing, reverse proxy, JWT authentication, unified error handling, and middleware support for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocation requests.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: SessionManager Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the Router needs to manage sessions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter  \n**WHEN** handling session-based routing requests  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851763952,"end":1775851763968}}}}
